  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Get cooking in Nepal with Solar Cookers Intl.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Nepal, usually it&apos;s women who cook. They face blockades, fuel crises and poverty. Cooking fuel is often unavailable. Free solar thermal energy is abundant. Goals:   Build solar cookers from locally available materials  Train/empower primarily women: elderly, orphans, disabled and others to obtain cooking/fuel security Protect family health from diseases due to indoor air pollution Reduce environmental and forest degradation  Encourage women to set up micro-businesses.</narrative>
  </description>
